{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Segoe UI;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs18 This program uses mgcrypt_GenerateRandom to generate a random number (transformed to hexadecimal digits). You can specify the number of random bytes to generate (:= blocksize). Due to the encoding with hexadecimal digits the length in bytes of the resulting string will be blocksize*2. \par
\par
The required memory for the result is allocated by the DLL function, no need to pass a Magic variable which will be filled with the result. You can use this random number, which is of cyrptographic strength for symmetric and assymetric keys, for initilaization vectors, salts, nonces, ..,\par
}

